# Typography System

## Font Families

### System Font Stack (Recommended)
```css
font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, 
             "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
```

### Platform-Specific
- **iOS/macOS**: SF Pro, -apple-system
- **Android**: Roboto
- **Windows**: Segoe UI
- **Web**: System font stack

### Monospace
```css
font-family: "SF Mono", "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", Consolas, 
             "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
```

## Type Scale

### Modular Scale (1.25 ratio - recommended)
- **12px** (0.75rem): Caption, metadata
- **14px** (0.875rem): Small body, labels
- **16px** (1rem): Body text (base)
- **20px** (1.25rem): Large body, H5
- **24px** (1.5rem): H4
- **32px** (2rem): H3
- **40px** (2.5rem): H2
- **48px** (3rem): H1
- **64px** (4rem): Display (hero headlines)

### Alternative Scale (1.333 ratio - more contrast)
- 12px, 16px, 21px, 28px, 37px, 50px, 66px

## Line Height

### Body Text
- **Minimum**: 1.4 (tight, for UI)
- **Recommended**: 1.5-1.6 (comfortable reading)
- **Maximum**: 1.8 (loose, for accessibility)

### Headings
- **Large headings** (H1-H2): 1.1-1.2 (tight)
- **Medium headings** (H3-H4): 1.2-1.3
- **Small headings** (H5-H6): 1.3-1.4

### UI Elements
- **Buttons**: 1.2-1.4
- **Labels**: 1.3-1.5
- **Input fields**: 1.4-1.5

## Font Weights

### Standard Weights
- **Light**: 300 (rare, large text only)
- **Regular**: 400 (body text)
- **Medium**: 500 (subheadings, emphasis)
- **Semibold**: 600 (headings)
- **Bold**: 700 (strong emphasis)

### Usage
- **Body text**: 400 (regular)
- **Headings**: 600-700 (semibold-bold)
- **Buttons**: 500-600 (medium-semibold)
- **Labels**: 400-500 (regular-medium)

## Line Length

### Optimal Reading
- **Ideal**: 50-75 characters per line
- **Acceptable**: 45-90 characters
- **Maximum**: 90 characters

### Implementation
```css
max-width: 65ch; /* 65 characters */
```

### Context
- **Articles/blogs**: 60-75 characters
- **UI text**: 45-60 characters
- **Wide layouts**: Up to 90 characters

## Letter Spacing

### Default
- **Body text**: Normal (0)
- **Small text** (< 14px): +0.01em to +0.02em
- **All caps**: +0.05em to +0.1em
- **Large headings**: -0.01em to -0.02em (optical adjustment)

### Avoid
- Tight letter spacing (< -0.02em) on body text
- Excessive spacing (> 0.1em) except for all caps

## Text Alignment

### Left-Aligned (Default)
- Body text
- Paragraphs
- Lists
- Forms
- Most UI elements

### Center-Aligned
- Hero headlines
- Modal titles
- Empty states
- Centered layouts only

### Right-Aligned
- Numbers in tables
- Dates
- Prices
- Navigation items (sometimes)

### Justified
- **Avoid** in UI (creates rivers of whitespace)
- Acceptable for print-style layouts with hyphenation

## Responsive Typography

### Mobile (< 640px)
- Reduce heading sizes by 10-20%
- Keep body text 14-16px minimum
- Increase line height slightly (1.6)

### Tablet (640-1023px)
- Standard sizes
- Line height 1.5-1.6

### Desktop (1024px+)
- Standard or slightly larger
- Line height 1.5
- Consider larger base size (18px) for marketing

### Fluid Typography
```css
font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.5vw, 1.25rem);
```

## Accessibility

### Minimum Sizes
- **Body text**: 14px (preferably 16px)
- **UI labels**: 12px minimum
- **Touch targets**: 14px minimum

### Contrast
- **Body text** (< 18px): 4.5:1 minimum
- **Large text** (≥ 18px): 3:1 minimum
- **Bold text** (≥ 14px bold): 3:1 minimum

### User Scaling
- Support browser zoom (200%+)
- Use relative units (rem, em)
- Test with large text settings

## Common Patterns

### Article/Blog
```css
h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; }
h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3; }
p  { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 65ch; }
```

### Application UI
```css
h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3; }
h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; }
p  { font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.5; }
```

### Data-Dense (Enterprise)
```css
h1 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3; }
h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; }
p  { font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.4; }
```

## Best Practices

### Do
- Use system fonts for performance
- Maintain consistent type scale
- Limit to 2-3 font weights
- Use relative units (rem, em)
- Test with user zoom
- Ensure sufficient contrast
- Limit line length for readability

### Don't
- Use more than 2 font families
- Use decorative fonts for body text
- Use light weights for small text
- Ignore line height
- Center long paragraphs
- Use justified text without hyphenation
- Rely on color alone for emphasis
